1.3
log
@Better pexp.
@
text
@#!/bin/sh
#
# $OpenBSD: postgrey.rc,v 1.2 2011/12/17 22:01:13 sthen Exp $

daemon="${TRUEPREFIX}/libexec/postgrey -d"
daemon_flags="--inet=10023"

. /etc/rc.d/rc.subr

pexp="perl: ${daemon}${daemon_flags:+ ${daemon_flags}}"

rc_cmd $1
@


1.2
log
@Where a program with an rc script _requires_ a certain command line
parameter to daemonize, move the parameter from daemon to daemon_flags,
so that the user cannot inadvertently prevent it from daemonizing by
adjusting the flags.

Discussed with ajacoutot and schwarze, this method was suggested
by schwarze@@ as a simpler alternative to my diff. ok aja@@
@
